1
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:27,600
Okkhun Wisanwaja.

2
00:00:38,890 --> 00:00:39,760
Get down!

3
00:02:26,860 --> 00:02:30,380
(Bangkok, 2026)

4
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:42,280
What happened?

5
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:44,200
He lost control of his motorcycle,

6
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:44,850
crashing a pillar.

7
00:02:44,850 --> 00:02:45,790
Now he’s unconscious,

8
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:46,710
unresponsive,

9
00:02:46,710 --> 00:02:48,240
and has bruises on his chest.

10
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:49,480
Thank you.

11
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,110
What’s the vital signs?

12
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:53,300
The vital signs BP is 80/60.

13
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,810
O₂ Sat is 80%.

14
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:56,160
Start two IV lines.

15
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:57,250
Draw pre-op labs.

16
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,240
And prepare 4 PRC blood units.

17
00:02:59,240 --> 00:02:59,730
Yes.

18
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:01,880
Sir.

19
00:03:02,470 --> 00:03:03,100
Sir.

20
00:03:03,670 --> 00:03:04,520
He is unconscious.

21
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,810
Keep holding the ambu bag.

22
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:07,770
Prepare for intubation. Size 7.5.

23
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,040
He may have pneumothorax.

24
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:17,020
Prepare the ICD

25
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:18,220
and the ventilator.

26
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:18,720
Yes.

27
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,520
Follow up on the X-ray.

28
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,829
And get an ultrasound machine.

29
00:03:22,829 --> 00:03:23,329
Yes.

30
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:48,770
The patient is ready.

31
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:49,560
Intubation completed.

32
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,310
O₂ Sat is 87%.

33
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:52,910
BP is 60/30.

34
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:54,690
Bleeding in the right chest cavity.

35
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,840
Oxygen at 100%.

36
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,940
Prepare for thoracotomy.

37
00:03:57,940 --> 00:03:58,520
Blade.

38
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:00,930
Blade.

39
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:05,250
O₂ Sat is 70%.

40
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:06,900
BP is 60/30.

41
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,750
Blood pressure is still dropping.

42
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,270
Extend the thoracotomy.

43
00:04:10,270 --> 00:04:11,250
Continue suction.

44
00:04:20,180 --> 00:04:21,760
Bleeding from the fractured right ribs.

45
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,920
It punctured the lung.

46
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,810
Clamp here.

47
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,010
Insert the chest tube.

48
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,540
Doctor, his heart has stopped.

49
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:29,280
Hold it there.

50
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:31,280
Start internal cardiac massage.

51
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,040
Adrenaline 1 milligram IV stat.

52
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,030
Adrenaline 1 milligram IV stat.

53
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,050
No heart rate.

54
00:05:07,650 --> 00:05:09,030
Time of death.

55
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,280
11:50 p.m.

56
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,370
Doctor.

57
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,590
How is my son?

58
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,280
He’s safe now, right?

59
00:05:32,670 --> 00:05:34,040
I’m sorry for your loss.

60
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,940
He lost a lot of blood.

61
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,080
His heart stopped during surgery.

62
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:39,400
Doctor.

63
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:45,600
This isn't true, right?

64
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,640
Doctor.

65
00:05:50,570 --> 00:05:51,360
Doctor.

66
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:54,350
Could you try to save my son again?

67
00:05:55,150 --> 00:05:59,100
Please try one more time, please.

68
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,320
I'm begging you.

69
00:06:42,330 --> 00:06:43,460
Give it some thought.

70
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:45,380
I won't approve the resignation letter yet.

71
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,890
Just take a break for now.

72
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:48,130
Take as long as you need.

73
00:06:48,490 --> 00:06:50,070
And come back when you’re ready.

74
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,320
Get plenty of rest.

75
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,110
We’ll always be waiting for you, Dr. Great.

76
00:07:27,310 --> 00:07:28,010
Hi, P’O.

77
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,070
Oh, hey.

78
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,320
How have you been?

79
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,220
It's been a while.

80
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:34,690
Why do you look so stressed?

81
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:39,800
Something happened at the hospital.

82
00:07:40,909 --> 00:07:41,450
Really?

83
00:07:41,450 --> 00:07:42,400
The hospital?

84
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:44,150
Anything to drink?

85
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:47,730
I’ll have the usual.

86
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:48,610
The usual.

87
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:49,320
Okay.

88
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,159
As you wish.

89
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:05,290
Here.

90
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,760
Same as always.

91
00:08:08,470 --> 00:08:09,050
Thank you.

92
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:29,500
Hey, guys.

93
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:31,880
There's just one table left.

94
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,870
You can go home first.

95
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:34,120
I’ll take care of the rest.

96
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,000
Go on, drive safely.

97
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:48,730
Hello?

98
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,160
Fine, fine.

99
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,180
I’ll get it for you.

100
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,820
Hey.

101
00:08:53,410 --> 00:08:54,840
Can you watch the shop for a bit?

102
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,120
Only that table is left.

103
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:58,280
I’m going upstairs to get my wife’s stuff.

104
00:08:58,990 --> 00:08:59,850
I'll leave it to you.

105
00:08:59,850 --> 00:09:00,440
Alright.

106
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:01,120
Okay.

107
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,510
Sir.

108
00:09:15,310 --> 00:09:16,250
The shop is closed.

109
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:17,880
None of my business.

110
00:09:18,810 --> 00:09:20,280
Over there.

111
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,430
If you hadn’t read my boss’s fortune like that,

112
00:09:27,430 --> 00:09:28,900
he wouldn’t have lost the auction.

113
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,170
It was not me.

114
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:36,310
It was your boss’s fate.

115
00:09:43,490 --> 00:09:44,000
Hey!

116
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:45,830
Stop!

117
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:46,990
F*ck off!

118
00:09:58,950 --> 00:09:59,630
Officer.

119
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,470
There’s a fight at my shop.

120
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:02,840
Please come right away.

121
00:10:03,220 --> 00:10:04,280
It’s urgent.

122
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,530
Is this yours?

123
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,280
Yes, thank you.

124
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:33,280
Can I repay you by reading your fortune?

125
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,390
I’m pretty accurate.

126
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,390
I don’t believe in fortune telling.

127
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,890
The Death?

128
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,800
It’s obvious then.

129
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,240
It's not about death.

130
00:10:53,150 --> 00:10:55,160
It means the change of fate.

131
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:59,400
Meeting and parting.

132
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:02,400
In other words,

133
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,390
you’re about to face...

134
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:07,080
the biggest change of your life.

135
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,790
What are you doing, Grandma?

136
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:40,560
Oh, my.

137
00:11:41,070 --> 00:11:42,800
Why didn’t you go to work today?

138
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:44,360
Uh…

139
00:11:44,590 --> 00:11:45,700
Is something wrong?

140
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:47,810
I’m on vacation leave.

141
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:48,620
I see.

142
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:49,480
That’s good.

143
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:52,140
You’ve been working hard for months.

144
00:11:52,140 --> 00:11:53,570
It’s good to take a break.

145
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:04,970
You had to open a recipe book?

146
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,950
12 Thai Desserts.

147
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:12,680
By Thao Thong Kip Ma.

148
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:14,730
Who is that?

149
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:15,750
What a funny name.

150
00:12:16,410 --> 00:12:16,850
Hey.

151
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:18,490
Don’t make fun of her.

152
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:20,460
She was the head of the royal dessert kitchen

153
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:21,860
for King Narai.

154
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:24,120
Her original name was Maria Guyomar.

155
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,920
But the name Thao Thong Kip Ma

156
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:28,080
was granted by King Narai.

157
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,080
And the desserts I make, thong yip, thong yod, and foi thong,

158
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:33,470
all came from her recipes.

159
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,700
Okay.

160
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:36,000
Khun Nualsipang.

161
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,700
Yes.

162
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,900
Enough for Thao Thong Kip Ma,

163
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,960
let’s talk about your health.

164
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,420
The doctor is here.

165
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,220
Hello, Grandma.

166
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:51,520
Hello.

167
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:53,400
Please come inside.

168
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,160
Sure.

169
00:12:58,510 --> 00:13:00,080
I’m perfectly fine.

170
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,330
Why are you making such a fuss?

171
00:13:02,330 --> 00:13:05,480
You refused to get a health checkup at the hospital,

172
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,680
so I asked the doctor to examine you here.

173
00:13:07,990 --> 00:13:10,080
It’s a bit too much, though.

174
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:12,310
I’m going to check your blood pressure.

175
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:22,320
What’s your name?

176
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,160
It's Lalana.

177
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,480
You can call me Jeab.

178
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,080
Okay.

179
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,150
You and…

180
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:30,750
Great…

181
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:31,880
Are you two…?

182
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:35,960
-No.
-No, grandma.

183
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:38,300
We're not.

184
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,330
Oh.

185
00:13:39,330 --> 00:13:40,400
Really?

186
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:42,120
Uh…

187
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:44,840
Your blood pressure is high.

188
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:45,870
Oh.

189
00:13:45,870 --> 00:13:47,200
I was stressed earlier.

190
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,000
Normally, it’s not…

191
00:13:48,330 --> 00:13:49,490
Khun Nualsipang.

192
00:13:49,780 --> 00:13:51,090
Please don’t argue with the doctor.

193
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:52,810
Alright.

194
00:13:56,180 --> 00:13:58,800
You need to take good care of yourself.

195
00:13:58,800 --> 00:13:59,600
Thank you, dear.

196
00:14:00,010 --> 00:14:00,950
Next week,

197
00:14:00,950 --> 00:14:02,720
you have an X-ray appointment.

198
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,110
If you refuse to go,

199
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:05,590
I’ll ask Dr. Jeab

200
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:07,700
to park an X-ray truck right here.

201
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:09,630
This grandson!

202
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:12,830
Thank you.

203
00:14:13,330 --> 00:14:16,060
Now I’ll draw some blood to check your sugar levels.

204
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,520
You eat a lot of sweets, right?

205
00:14:18,740 --> 00:14:19,920
Will it hurt?

206
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,280
It’s like an ant bite.

207
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,710
Ant bites hurt, you know.

208
00:14:23,670 --> 00:14:24,430
It won’t hurt.

209
00:14:29,450 --> 00:14:53,860
(chanting)

210
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:32,370
Grandma.

211
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:33,160
Yes?

212
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,160
I’ll be right back.

213
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:45,910
What’s up, Rit?

214
00:17:47,390 --> 00:17:48,250
Alright.

215
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:49,120
I’ll help out.

216
00:18:13,220 --> 00:18:17,610
(Ayutthaya, year 1036 of Thai minor era)

217
00:18:29,290 --> 00:18:31,920
Come live with us, Gaew.

218
00:18:33,060 --> 00:18:34,210
Jumpa and I

219
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:36,400
will raise you

220
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:39,710
as if you were our own child.

221
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:41,880
Yes, sir.

222
00:18:43,690 --> 00:18:45,720
You poor thing.

223
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:48,360
Losing your parents at such a young age.

224
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,710
Make yourself at home here.

225
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,170
Your mother,

226
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:56,120
Pudjeeb,

227
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:58,280
was my younger cousin.

228
00:18:58,620 --> 00:19:00,120
And your father

229
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:02,950
was my fellow disciple.

230
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:05,290
You’re not a stranger to us.

231
00:19:07,930 --> 00:19:09,360
Thank you very much.

232
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:15,630
Gaew.

233
00:19:17,090 --> 00:19:18,400
That’s Si

234
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,700
and Dech,

235
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:21,410
your older cousins.

236
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:27,860
P’Si.

237
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:29,280
P’Dech.

238
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:31,790
Greetings.

239
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:37,440
Dech.

240
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,320
Si.

241
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:39,700
From now on,

242
00:19:40,130 --> 00:19:41,150
Gaew...

243
00:19:41,150 --> 00:19:42,840
is your younger brother.

244
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,320
Yes, sir.

245
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,270
Gaew.

246
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:47,890
Come here.

247
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:52,610
Dech, you too.

248
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:25,320
Hold out your hands.

249
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:44,590
From this day on,

250
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:47,060
you two are true friends.

251
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,350
Cherish this friendship

252
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:51,840
and don’t abandon each other.

253
00:20:52,350 --> 00:20:54,630
May the gods watch over this friendship

254
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:57,510
and let it last

255
00:20:57,510 --> 00:21:00,510
until the end of time.

256
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:19,360
Yay!

257
00:21:22,330 --> 00:21:23,000
Woo!

258
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,200
Yam.

259
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:44,180
Is Thongkam ready for me?

260
00:21:44,410 --> 00:21:46,080
Yes, Lord Gaew.

261
00:21:46,670 --> 00:21:47,450
Today

262
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:49,650
is the day I get even with them.

263
00:21:57,820 --> 00:21:59,080
Thongkam, go!

264
00:21:59,430 --> 00:21:59,990
Go!

265
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,040
Damn it!

266
00:22:29,870 --> 00:22:30,890
My rooster lost.

267
00:22:30,890 --> 00:22:32,040
Then yours should die too!

268
00:22:34,950 --> 00:22:36,150
Don’t you dare touch it!

269
00:22:36,490 --> 00:22:37,390
Then I’ll touch you.

270
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:54,190
Hey!

271
00:22:55,610 --> 00:22:56,430
Saen, you…!

272
00:22:59,350 --> 00:22:59,760
Get up.

273
00:23:00,970 --> 00:23:02,320
This way, my lord.

274
00:23:09,890 --> 00:23:10,760
Stop this instant!

275
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:27,490
P’Dech, don't meddle!

276
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:32,950
This is between me, Wat, and Saen.

277
00:23:33,990 --> 00:23:36,250
Stop while I’m still asking nicely.

278
00:23:36,930 --> 00:23:37,920
You bastard.

279
00:23:39,110 --> 00:23:39,930
What the hell?

280
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:40,930
Hey, hey.

281
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:48,330
You're being nosy, P’Dech.

282
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:50,770
Ow!

283
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:03,150
When we're home,

284
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:04,290
you’re in big trouble.

285
00:24:19,430 --> 00:24:20,600
Go, go.

286
00:24:21,210 --> 00:24:22,360
Get out.

287
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:24,360
Yam, we’re leaving!

288
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:45,810
Gaew.

289
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,360
I’m not done with you yet.

290
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,440
Haven’t you done enough?

291
00:25:02,210 --> 00:25:04,210
You’re acting like a street thug.

292
00:25:04,990 --> 00:25:06,980
You can’t speak to me like this!

293
00:25:07,870 --> 00:25:09,010
Why can’t I?

294
00:25:10,270 --> 00:25:12,000
Father told me to look after you.

295
00:25:12,330 --> 00:25:14,000
You’re like my younger brother.

296
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:16,000
So when you do wrong,

297
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,220
I have to punish you!

298
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:19,150
I’m the son of a high lord.

299
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:20,550
What can you do to me?

300
00:25:24,410 --> 00:25:25,600
How about a few lashes?

301
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:30,990
Let go.

302
00:25:33,270 --> 00:25:33,880
Let go!

303
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:40,640
My lord!

304
00:25:42,430 --> 00:25:43,160
My lord.

305
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:43,710
Ow!

306
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:46,270
Ow!

307
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:48,200
Stop!

308
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:52,960
Someone as shameless as you

309
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,700
has to be punished.

310
00:25:55,510 --> 00:25:56,390
If not you,

311
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:57,310
then your servant!

312
00:25:57,670 --> 00:25:58,700
If you want to punish,

313
00:25:59,630 --> 00:26:00,860
punish me!

314
00:26:08,780 --> 00:26:09,450
Pin.

315
00:26:09,970 --> 00:26:10,850
Let’s go back.

316
00:26:10,850 --> 00:26:11,510
Yes, sir.

317
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:20,380
P’Muen crossed the line,

318
00:26:21,450 --> 00:26:22,970
I’ll make him pay no matter what.

319
00:26:22,970 --> 00:26:23,790
My lord.

320
00:26:23,980 --> 00:26:26,290
Please don’t do anything bad.

321
00:26:30,910 --> 00:26:31,570
Yam.

322
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:32,840
Get ready.

323
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:38,190
Tomorrow,

324
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:40,580
I heard that P’Muen...

325
00:26:41,210 --> 00:26:43,150
is going to run an errand for Aunt Jumpa.

326
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:02,510
Go sink his boat.

327
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:06,040
Please don’t.

328
00:27:06,780 --> 00:27:08,310
He can’t swim.

329
00:27:08,950 --> 00:27:10,300
What if he falls

330
00:27:10,810 --> 00:27:11,870
into the water?

331
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:15,130
P’Muen won’t die that easily.

332
00:27:16,050 --> 00:27:17,510
I just want to teach him a lesson.

333
00:27:18,220 --> 00:27:19,410
Someone will help him.

334
00:27:20,070 --> 00:27:22,050
He humiliated me in front of Wat.

335
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:23,210
Pure disrespect!

336
00:27:25,330 --> 00:27:27,210
I still don’t dare.

337
00:27:28,020 --> 00:27:28,970
So I have to do it?

338
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:33,390
But…

339
00:27:33,390 --> 00:27:34,600
Are you going on your own,

340
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:35,850
or do I have to kick you off?

341
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:37,210
I understand.

342
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:43,770
Go!

343
00:27:45,550 --> 00:27:46,330
I’m going.

344
00:28:12,770 --> 00:28:14,290
Huh?

345
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,170
What happened?

346
00:28:16,170 --> 00:28:17,260
What is this?

347
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:19,750
My lady.

348
00:28:20,730 --> 00:28:21,390
My lady!

349
00:28:21,550 --> 00:28:22,370
My lady!

350
00:28:22,830 --> 00:28:24,730
Lady Jumpa fell into the water!

351
00:28:25,990 --> 00:28:26,960
Hey, you!

352
00:28:29,790 --> 00:28:30,550
My lady!

353
00:28:31,050 --> 00:28:34,150
My lady!

354
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,760
My lady!

355
00:28:45,050 --> 00:28:45,890
My lord.

356
00:28:46,890 --> 00:28:47,770
My lord.

357
00:28:48,490 --> 00:28:50,270
It wasn’t Lord Dech on the boat.

358
00:28:50,270 --> 00:28:51,120
It was...

359
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:53,210
Lady Jumpa.

360
00:28:53,460 --> 00:28:54,410
What?

361
00:29:10,910 --> 00:29:11,610
My lady.

362
00:29:14,070 --> 00:29:15,960
Is anyone else still in the water?

363
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:17,310
Noi.

364
00:29:17,910 --> 00:29:19,310
Noi disappeared.

365
00:29:19,310 --> 00:29:20,560
She hasn’t come back up.

366
00:29:20,810 --> 00:29:21,560
Noi?

367
00:29:21,900 --> 00:29:22,590
Waen.

368
00:29:22,910 --> 00:29:24,640
Search everywhere for her!

369
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:25,430
Yes, ma’am.

370
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:28,000
Khiao.

371
00:29:28,390 --> 00:29:29,040
Yes?

372
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,990
Tell people at the house

373
00:29:30,990 --> 00:29:32,500
to come help right now!

374
00:29:32,970 --> 00:29:33,780
-Yes, ma’am.
-Go!

375
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:35,230
Juang.

376
00:29:35,230 --> 00:29:35,700
Yes?

377
00:29:35,700 --> 00:29:36,650
How are you?

378
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:38,950
I’m fine.

379
00:29:39,570 --> 00:29:40,940
Stay strong.

380
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:45,310
Someone deliberately sank my boat!

381
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:50,280
